incom 5/13/2024 12:45 PM
After reviewing several scientific articles, I found several to say that the research of BHT as a carcinogen (substance which increases the risk of cancer) is limited in humans. It has been tested on rats, two tests determining opposite conclusions, one for rate of increased cancer, and one for the rate of decreased cancer. All of the 4-5 sources determined BHT to be safe (dates ranging from 1999-2024). I believe that it is not something to be overly cautious of, but overconsumption should definitely have negative health impacts, just as all processed foods (especially in america).
